ntHits
------------------------------------------
ntHits is a tool for efficiently counting and filtering k-mers based on their
frequencies.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.5.0-0.477.gd5dcb484c705
  libbtllib1-1.6.2-1bl1
  libgcc1-11.4.0-1
  libgomp1-11.4.0-1
  libstdc++6-11.4.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.41-3
  cygport-0.36.7-1
  gcc-core-11.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-11.4.0-1
  libbtllib-devel-1.6.2-1bl1
  meson-1.1.1-1
  ninja-1.11.1-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/bcgsc/ntHits

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/bcgsc/ntHits.git

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack ntHits-1.0.2-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./ntHits-1.0.2-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/ntHits-1.0.2-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/ntHits-1.0.2-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(ntHits)
  /usr/bin/nthits-bfq.exe
  /usr/bin/nthits.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/ntHits.README
  /usr/share/doc/ntHits/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/ntHits/README.md
  /usr/share/doc/ntHits/nthits-logo.png

